  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has published its final report on guidelines for the authorisation of third-country branches under the Capital Requirements Directive, providing clarity for banks operating in the EU. In Belgium, the financial regulator has begun enforcing the Markets in Crypto-Assets regulation by warning six unauthorized crypto firms, marking a significant step in the country's implementation of the EU's crypto regulatory framework. The Anti-Money Laundering Authority is also consulting on draft implementing technical standards for reporting suspicions and providing transaction records, aiming to enhance anti-money laundering efforts. The European Securities and Markets Authority has launched a consultation on technical advice for selected Key Performance Indicators under the Taxonomy Disclosures Delegated Act, seeking to simplify sustainability reporting.",
